     ,"INC-SPECT":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["A 48Ca11+ beam was produced from isotopically"
		,"enriched 48Ca [95.99(2) %] using the Versatile ECR"
		,"for Nuclear Science (VENUS) ion source and injected"
		,"into the 88-Inch Cyclotron at LBNL. There, it was"
		,"accelerated to a nominal energy of 256 MeV before"
		,"being extracted from the cyclotron. The average beam"
		,"current at the exit of the cyclotron was 8.3e microA"
		,"or 4.7*10**12 ions/s. At the beginning and end of the"
		,"experimental campaign, the beam energy was determined"
		,"by nondestructively measuring the time-of-flight of"
		,"individual beam pulses between two fast-current"
		,"transformers separated by 3.563(5) m along a"
		,"neighboring beamline. The beam energy was measured"
		,"to be 258.4(25) and 259.0(25) MeV, respectively."
		,"Directly following the differential pumping section,"
		,"the beam impinged on a rotating target wheel composed"
		,"of four arc-shaped segments with a diameter of 12.2"
		,"cm. The average beam energy in the target was"
		,"240.7(30) MeV, leading to an average excitation"
		,"energy of 39(2) MeV."]
	}
      ]
     ,"DETECTOR":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"MAGSP", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Magnetic spectrometer"}
	    ,{"code":"SISD", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Silicon strip detector"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" The Berkeley Gas-filled Separator (BGS),"
		,"the newly installed Superheavy Recoil detector (SHREC),"
		," along with an upgraded digital electronics and data"
		,"acquisition system. SHREC consists of an implantation"
		,"detector that is comprised of three double-sided"
		,"silicon-strip detectors (DSSDs), each with an active"
		,"area of 58.5mmx58.5mm, a thickness of 325 microm, and"
		,"an average deadlayer thickness of 1.5 microm. Each"
		,"DSSD is subdivided into 58 strips on both the front"
		,"and back sides."]
	}
      ]
     ,"SAMPLE":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["A rotating target wheel composed of four arc-shaped"
		,"segments with a diameter of 12.2 cm. Each segment"
		,"consisted of a 2.0(1)-microm-thick natTi foil onto"
		,"which an average of 0.44(4) mg/cm2 of 244Pu (as"
		,"244PuO2) was added via molecular plating."
		,"Measured thicknesses of target segments and estimated"
		,"range of beam energies and excitation through the"
		,"target according to energy-loss measurements,"
		,"experimental masses for 48Ca and 244Pu, along with the"
		,"theoretical mass for 292Fl:"
		,"Segment    Thickness  Beam energy           E*"
		,"           (mg/cm2)   (MeV)                 (MeV)"
		,"1          0.39(5)    243.7-238.3           41.2-37.2"
		,"2          0.42(4)    243.7-237.9           41.2-36.9"
		,"3          0.47(5)    243.7-237.2           41.2-36.3"
		,"4          0.45(7)    243.7-237.4           41.2-36.5"
		,"Average    0.44(4)    243.7-237.7           41.2-36.7"]
	}
      ]
     ,"METHOD":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"REC", "dict":"METHOD", "idict":21,"hlp":"Collection of recoils"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" During the experimental campaign, the 244Pu"
		,"target was irradiated for 6.5 days. The Fl"
		,"evaporation residues (EVR) of interest were separated"
		,"from the unreacted beam and unwanted reaction"
		,"products inside the BGS based on their differing"
		,"magnetic rigidities (Brho) in helium gas. For the"
		,"first 3.9 days of the experiment, the BGS was set to"
		,"bend products with Brho=2.25Tm to the center of the"
		,"Superheavy Recoil detector (SHREC). This was then"
		,"increased to Brho=2.34Tm for the remainder of the"
		,"experiment. At the BGS focal plane, the separated"
		,"EVRs were implanted into the newly constructed SHREC"
		,"detector."]
	}
      ]
     ,"ERR-ANALYS":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":{"header":"ERR-SYS"
	     ,"headerHelp":"Total systematic uncertainty"}
	,"x4freetext":[" Systematic uncertainties on the cross"
		,"sections measured at the BGS result from five main"
		,"contributions. Error propagation of the five sources"
		,"of uncertainty indicates that the systematic error on"
		,"cross sections reported at the BGS are 12%."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":{"header":"ERR-1"
	     ,"headerHelp":"1st partial uncertainty, defined under ERR-ANALYS"}
	,"x4freetext":[" The first is the uncertainty in the"
		,"efficiency for transporting EVRs to the SHREC"
		,"detector. This error was estimated by sending EVRs of"
		,"254No from the 208Pb(48Ca,2n) reaction through the"
		,"BGS and comparing the size and shape of the 254No"
		,"implantation distribution on the focal plane detector"
		,"to distributions that were modeled using the"
		,"simulation code. Based on this comparison, it is"
		,"estimated that the error on the EVR collection"
		,"efficiency is sigmaeff/eff=10%."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":{"header":"ERR-2"
	     ,"headerHelp":"2nd partial uncertainty, defined under ERR-ANALYS"}
	,"x4freetext":[" The second is the uncertainty in the angle of"
		,"the Rutherford detectors is 0.1 degree with respect"
		,"to the beam axis. For the beam used in this"
		,"experiment, this results in a 3% uncertainty in the"
		,"Rutherford cross section and a corresponding 3%"
		,"uncertainty in the calculated EVR cross section."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":{"header":"ERR-3"
	     ,"headerHelp":"3rd partial uncertainty, defined under ERR-ANALYS"}
	,"x4freetext":[" A third contribution is due to the fact that"
		,"upstream of each Rutherford detector is a collimator"
		,"that reduces the number of scattered particles"
		,"impacting the detectors. The uncertainty in the size"
		,"of this collimator is the main contribution to"
		,"uncertainty in the angle subtended by this collimator"
		,"and is estimated to contribute 4% to the systematic"
		,"error in the cross sections."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":{"header":"ERR-4"
	     ,"headerHelp":"4th partial uncertainty, defined under ERR-ANALYS"}
	,"x4freetext":[" Two attenuation screens are situated between"
		,"the target and the Rutherford detectors to reduce the"
		,"intensity of Rutherford-scattered particle impacting"
		,"the detectors, and introduce a fourth source of"
		,"uncertainty. It is estimated that the uncertainty in"
		,"the attenuation factor contributes 5% to the"
		,"systematic error."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":{"header":"ERR-5"
	     ,"headerHelp":"5th partial uncertainty, defined under ERR-ANALYS"}
	,"x4freetext":[" The last contribution to the systematic"
		,"uncertainty comes from the uncertainty in the"
		,"absolute energy from the 88-Inch Cyclotron, which is"
		,"estimated to be 1%. While the beam energy was"
		,"measured to a higher precision than that for this"
		,"experiment, that measurement was performed on a"
		,"neighboring beamline. It is not certain that the same"
		,"turn out of the cyclotron, and therefore the same"
		,"beam energy, is extracted for both beamlines."]
	}
      ]
